\int_0^\infty\frac{|\cos(x)|}{x+1} dx
\int_{n\pi}^{(n+1)\pi} |\cos x| \,\mathrm{d}x = 2
\int_{n\pi}^{(n+1)\pi} \frac{|\cos x| \,\mathrm{d}x}{x+1} \ge \int_{n\pi}^{(n+1)\pi} \frac{|\cos x| \,\mathrm{d}x}{(n+2)\pi} = \frac{2}{(n+2)\pi}
\int_{0}^{\infty} \frac{|\cos x| \,\mathrm{d}x}{x+1} \ge \frac1\pi \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac1{k+2}=\infty.
